                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17114867" author="bn75" created="Sat, 23 May 2020 16:19:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i have solved the problem, how should i upload the changes?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17114868" author="tilman" created="Sat, 23 May 2020 16:25:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please attach a diff / patch file that is against the trunk. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17114884" author="tilman" created="Sat, 23 May 2020 16:52:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That is a screenshot. Your IDE should allow to save this into a file. Please do also test your change with all 4 angle files from the other issue to be sure it works at any angle. And make sure that the old change still works.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17114898" author="tilman" created="Sat, 23 May 2020 17:13:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Your change doesn&apos;t work, it fails when using rot0.pdf as base file and background.pdf as overlay file. (but works with the old code)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, with &quot;diff / patch&quot; I mean a file that shows the differences only. I&apos;m not refusing the patch (I did the diff myself), but it is something that you should learn because it is useful with many projects. This is some feature that is likely in your IDE. You also need to work with the trunk, see here  &lt;a href=&quot;https://pdfbox.apache.org/building.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://pdfbox.apache.org/building.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17114900" author="tilman" created="Sat, 23 May 2020 17:16:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I realize that we need to introduce a proper testing, i.e. compare the rendering of file(s) that has been overlayed successfully with files where it is to be done. This way anybody trying a change could run the tests and see if something existing is broken.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17115123" author="bn75" created="Sun, 24 May 2020 11:07:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I already have the trunk and git installed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Where in the trunk do you want me to create the test to evaluate that the changes made in Overlay.java are correct?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Greetings,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Jairo.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17115125" author="tilman" created="Sun, 24 May 2020 11:10:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t worry, I&apos;m working on that one. Until it is done (maybe today, maybe not) you&apos;ll have to test manually.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17115151" author="jira-bot" created="Sun, 24 May 2020 11:31:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1878080 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1878080&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1878080&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4840&quot; title=&quot;Overlay doesn&amp;#39;t work properly when page is rotated&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4840&quot;&gt;PDFBOX-4840&lt;/a&gt;: add test files for upcoming test&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17115158" author="jira-bot" created="Sun, 24 May 2020 11:55:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1878082 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1878082&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1878082&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4840&quot; title=&quot;Overlay doesn&amp;#39;t work properly when page is rotated&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4840&quot;&gt;PDFBOX-4840&lt;/a&gt;: add regression test&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17115159" author="tilman" created="Sun, 24 May 2020 11:57:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Done. So now you can run the build and see whether your changes alter anything in existing behavior. If something breaks, the model PDFs are in &quot;pdfbox/src/test/resources/org/apache/pdfbox/multipdf&quot;, and the (possibly) &quot;wrong&quot; result PDFs are in &quot;pdfbox/target/test-output/overlay&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17115986" author="bn75" created="Mon, 25 May 2020 12:25:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would like to know the appropriate settings to be able to compile and download the dependencies of the project. At this moment I have maven installed but I am not able to download dependencies from the command line. I also can&apos;t compile the project and generate the jar for testing. Any ideas?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Greetings,&lt;br/&gt;
Jairo.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17116125" author="tilman" created="Mon, 25 May 2020 15:50:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;use commands below on windows. Directories may be different, you should go to the project directory, set JAVA_HOME and M2_HOME, and then run &quot;mvn install&quot;. Good luck.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;cd C:\Users\YOURNAME\Documents\Java\PDFBox reactor&lt;br/&gt;
SET JAVA_HOME=C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-14.0.1&lt;br/&gt;
SET M2_HOME=C:\Program Files\Apache Software Foundation\apache-maven-3.6.3&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;C:\Program Files\Apache Software Foundation\apache-maven-3.6.3\bin\mvn.cmd&quot; install&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
</comment>
